Thulani Gqirana, News24(Nielen de Klerk, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - More than R1m worth of counterfeit goods were confiscated in Cape Town over the weekend, police said on Monday.Spokesperson Constable Lucas Nofemela said police received information about a truck on the N1 heading for Cape Town suspected to be transporting counterfeit goods on Saturday.The courier company vehicle was stopped and searched. Counterfeit brand-name goods estimated to be worth around R1.2m were confiscated.No arrests had been made and police were still investigating, Nofemela said.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.